rvices - New York, NY			January 2005 to February 2019\nProvision of guidance to head of Divisions and other staff in the interpretation of policies under UN Rules and Regulations, and responses to inquiries regarding entitlements and benefits, administrative procedures. Administration of staff appointments using ERP tool, reviewing and processing requests as prescribed within the HR Partner functional role and delegated authority. Analysis of rebuttal cases/other litigations and providing responses as part of the organization’s administration of justice system. Revision of personnel records and determination of staff members\' eligibility for HR entitlements including mobility incentive. Processing departmental requests for onboarding of staff using Inspira Offer Management system and preparing Offer of Appointments. Induction of incoming staff and debriefing/guiding outgoing staff.  Administration of time and attendance, approving leave entries in Employee self-service, sick leave audit in relation to cases of exhaustion of the full-pay sick leave entitlement, and issuing recommendations to Medical Services for disability cases.\n\nAdministrative Assistant\nUnited Nations Mission in Mali – Bamako						October 2014 to December 2015\n(Temporary Assignment)\nProvision of office management and providing responses to a range of communications, preparing, processing and classifying confidential information, code cables; handling administrative duties/processes (e.g. leave and attendance records, travel arrangements, visa applications, expense reports, telecommunications charges, conference room bookings, etc.). Point of contact and liaison with senior officials, screening and prioritizing incoming correspondence, compiling background documents and references, identifying issues requiring manager\'s attention and referring others to relevant staff, researching, compiling and summarizing background materials for preparation of reports, briefs, speeches, etc. Demonstration of initiative in identifying and resolving problems in the context of work assignments and functions; managing highly confidential and sensitive matters; and appropriately applying relevant policies, guidelines, procedures and processes.\n\nAdministrative Assistant\nUnited Nations in Liberia – Monrovia							April 2009 to April 2011\n(Temporary Assignment)\nProvision of office management and acting as focal point for Training, HR administration, Recruitment, and Finance. Liaison with Human Resources for recruitment, classification of posts, and delivery of advice to staff on their entitlements under Staff Rules and Regulations. Preparation of budget submissions, and finalization of performance reports, analyzing variances between approved budgets and actual expenditures to request redeployment of funds and reallocation of resources. Processing and classifying confidential information; handling administrative duties/processes (e.g. leave and attendance records, travel arrangements, visa applications, expense statements, telecommunications charges, conference room bookings, etc.). Point of contact and liaison with senior officials, screening and prioritizing incoming correspondence, researching, compiling and summarizing background materials for use in preparation of reports, briefs, speeches, etc. \n\nHR Assistant/Administrative Assistant\nUnited Nations Department of Peacekeeping Operations - New York, NY			December 2002 to January 2005\nSupport to UN Field Missions by performing a full range of HR Functions in the administration of appointments and entitlements of international staff members based in Peacekeeping Operations at family and non-family duty stations. Provision of guidance to local Personnel Sections in accordance with staff rules, regulations, policies, and various Administrative Instructions. Using a specifically designed management system in the process of appointments, promotions, separations, and other entitlements and benefits. Monitoring of contractual status and initiation of actions for renewal of appointments and separations; administering rebuttal cases and other litigations, responding to the Administrative Tribunal’s motions. Maintaining accurate attendance records and monitoring records of staff members on long term sick leave for disability recommendation to Medical Services as necessary.\nPublic Information Assistant\nUnited Nations Department of Public Information - New York, NY				September 2002 to December 2002\nProvision of support to the UN General Assembly by issuing daily press releases on ongoing debates in French: Typing, correcting edited copies; formatting, printing and issuing final versions to be dispersed by e-mail and posted to the internet. \n\nAdministrative Assistant/Translator\nMiriam Home and Services - Montréal, QC 						February 2002 to June 2002\nPerformance of administrative duties as well as translation services for a team of twenty health professionals in the provision of rehabilitation and social integration services to persons (children, adolescents and adults) with intellectual disabilities and/or autism spectrum disorders and help them reach their full potential as individuals. Maintenance of office supplies inventory and replenishment of stock for the office, keeping the office library, ordering books and articles as may be necessary, tracking staff schedule and attendance records. Performing all translations, which were previously contracted outside the office as well as supporting clients, families when necessary.  \n\nAssistant to the Chief of Human Resources\nUnited Nations Office for Project Services - New York, NY 				December 2000 to November 2001\nProvision of support to the Assistant Director in a variety of tasks to ensure smooth and timely coordination of actions pertaining to the division’s responsibilities and activities.   Maintaining office supplies inventory and replenishing stock for the division on a regular basis.   Assisting in the organization of retreats and workshops, including market research for venue and accommodation, program arrangements and logistics.   Managing the Assistant Director office’s budget, including but not limited to reallocation of resources and providing procedural advice to staff.  Receiving and screening incoming mail, ensuring proper distribution and record within the Section.  Maintaining the Assistant Director’s calendar and making travel arrangements/authorization and expense reports.\n\nPublic Information Assistant\nUnited Nations Department of Public Information - New York, NY				August 2000 to December 2000\nProvision of support in issuing daily press releases in French: Typing, correcting edited copies; formatting, printing and issuing final versions to be circulated by e-mail and posted to the internet.\n\nContracts Specialist\nUnited States Agency for International Development (USAID) - Port au Prince		March 1995 to August 2000\nPrincipal assistant to the Contracting Officer in administering the full range of contracting and procurement actions, developing RFPs and advising Technical Evaluation Committees on responsiveness of proposals, applicability of the Federal Acquisition Regulations, etc. Performing Price/Cost analysis of proposals; Providing advisory services to project officers, procurement personnel and contractors on applicability and interpretation of procurement regulations. Responsibilities also included job classification, management of recruitment from the preparation of vacancy announcements in accordance with US Government regulations, establishment of selection committees, evaluation of applications for a short-list of candidates to be interviewed. Upon selection of candidates, revision of the selection process for compliance and initiation of the recruitment process including negotiations of salaries, verification of background, educational and security references.\n\nProgram Assistant\nUnited States Agency for International Development (USAID) - Port au Prince		October 1993 to March 1995\nDrafting of project narratives with prescribed formats using A.I.D. program guidance.  Application of Mission\'s funding and disbursement policies in preparing budgets and funding documents; coordination and facilitation of administrative support for the Democracy, Education, Elections and Justice Projects.  Coordination of all documentation and supporting materials required for on-going or new projects, ensuring that submissions are timely and in accordance with AID procedures.  Monitoring selected aspects of projects to obtain specific status information on a recurring basis.  Assistance in the programming, development, management and evaluation of the Democracy Enhancement and Administration of Justice projects.\n\nEducation\nAssociate degree in Technical Business Administration\nChrist the King Business School - Port au Prince, Haiti (October 1987 to June 1989)\n\nHigh school diploma (French Baccalaureate Part 2)\nSacred Heart Institution - Port au Prince, Haiti (October 1979 to June 1985)\n\nSkills\n• ERP Systems • Translation • Human Resources Management • Payroll • Research • Administrative and Office Management • Recruitment \n• Negotiation • Onboarding and Employee Orientation • Budgeting • Procurement • Logistics • Microsoft Office • Event Planning \n• Benefits Administration • Performance Management • Calendar Management\n\nLanguages\n• English and French - Expert','1','2026-03-10 18:19:37','2026-03-10 18:19:37',1),(26,'Rinkesh Patel','rikspatel24@gmail.com','8483489951','looking for job','I am holding MSc & BSc Chemistry degree..','1','2026-03-19 01:30:09','2026-03-19 01:30:09',2),(27,'Earl Wild','earl0305@msn.com','8482502158','Machine Installer/Operator and Handyman','Unable to copy and paste - I have provided a link to my resume.\n\nhttps://1drv.ms/w/c/bcb5205c559f73a9/IQACsb5YLtAtSaRZ2nrPSwrcAc-ZTYszdj7iDWOvQqJnZ7E?e=25dho4','1','2026-04-08 00:22:50','2026-04-08 00:22:50',4);
