,\"Hazmat: NO\",\"Molecular Weight: 60.08 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:54','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8338,'DEXTRATE NF (EMDEX)','100989','GCC','66828-18-0','1','dextrate-nf-emdex','Fine white odorless powder',NULL,'EMDEX- is a directly compressible, 100% water-soluble, and lactose-free tablet binder. It consists of glucose monohydrate and different polysaccharides derived from starch. Was designed for applications such as chewable, ingestible, dispersible, effervescent, and soluble tablets. It is also commonly used in veterinary applications.','Dextrate NF (Emdex);T/N: Unistrate D; Corn Syrup Dehydrated; T/N: Emdex Dextrates USP NF; Dextrates','Slightly hygroscopic. Store in well closed containers to prevent moisture exposure and to avoid contamination.','[\"50 lb. Bag\",\"50 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Industrial\"]','[\"Binders\"]',NULL,'[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: N\\/A\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: NO\",\"Molecular Weight: N\\/A\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:54','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8339,'DEXTRIN POWDER','100990','GCC','9004-53-9','1','dextrin-powder','Off-white to yellow powder','White dextrins are used as a crispness enhancer for food processing, in food batters, coatings, and glazes, (E number 1400), a textile finishing and coating agent to increase weight and stiffness of textile fabrics, a thickening and binding agent in pharmaceuticals and paper coatings.\r\nAs pyrotechnic binder and fuel, they are added to fireworks and sparklers, allowing them to solidify as pellets or \"stars.\"','Yellow dextrins are used as water-soluble glues in remoistable envelope adhesives and paper tubes, in the mining industry as additives in froth flotation, in the foundry industry as green strength additives in sand casting, as printing thickener for batik resist dyeing, and as binders in gouache paint and also in the leather industry.','Dextrin Powder; Unidex D; Pinedex; Starch Gum; Dextrine White; Dextrin Hydrate','Keep in a tightly closed container. Store in a cool, dry, ventilated area. Protect against physical damage.','[\"250 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"500 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"100 lb. Bag\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Industrial\",\"Food & bev.\",\"Pharmaceutical\"]','[\"Thickeners\",\"binders\",\"coating and sealants chemicals\",\"gums\"]',NULL,'[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 S 2 CL 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 477\\u00f8C\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: NO\",\"Molecular Weight: 504.43 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:54','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8340,'DEXTROMETHORPHAN HYDROBROMIDE MONOHYDRATE USP','100991','GCC','6700-34-1','1','dextromethorphan-hydrobromide-monohydrate-usp','White powder',NULL,'Most commonly used as a cough suppressant drug and is an active ingredient in most cough medicines. It is also used in a range of other medicines, from psychological to pain relief applications. It comes in several forms, either as a syrup, lozenge, spray, or tablet.','Dextromethorphan Hydrobromide MH USP; Unaphan DHBM; (9S,13S,14S)-3-Methoxy-17-methylmorphinan hydrobromide','Keep container tightly closed in a cool, dry well-ventilated area away from incompatible substances.','[\"50 Gram Bottle\",\"1 kg. HDPE WM Bottle\",\"5 kg. HDPE OH Pail\",\"25 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"25 kg. Fiber Drum\",\"50 kg. Fiber Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Pharmaceutical\"]','[\"Active pharmaceutical ingredient\"]','C18H28BrNO2','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 1 year from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 S 2 CL 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 116.2\\u00f8C\",\"Melting Point: 116-119\\u00f8C\",\"API: YES\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 370.32 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:54','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8341,'DEXTROSE ANHYDROUS FOOD GRADE','100992