ody cleaners, e.g. face cleansing creams, cream shampoos and hand cleaning pastes.','Disodium Lauryl Sulfosuccinate; T/N: Unimate DLS; T/N: Macinate LO; T/N: Rewopol SB F 12P; Butanedioic Acid, Sulfo-, C-dodecyl Ester, Disodium Salt; Disodium 4-Dodecyl 2-Sulphonatosuccinate','Storage or handling temperatures above 80øC are not recommended and will result in fairly rapid hydrolysis. Keep in cool, dry, well-ventilated area.','[\"250 ml. HDPE Bottle\",\"40 lb. Blue TH Pail\",\"450 lb. Liquipak\",\"1 lb.Bulk\"]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[\"Foam & viscosity boosters\",\"surfactants\"]','C16H29NaO7S','[\"Origin: Vegetable\\/ Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC48580 S3 CL55\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: >93o C (200oF)\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 412.45 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8449,'DISODIUM N-TALLON BETA-IMINODIPROPIONIC ACID','101112','GCC','61791-56-8','1','disodium-n-tallon-beta-iminodipropionic-acid','SURFACTANT FOR HIGHLY ACIDIC AND ALKALINE CLEANERS, SUBSTANTIVE TO FABRICS.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'KEEP WELL VFNTILATED.','[null]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[null]',NULL,'[null]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8450,'DISODIUM OLEAMIDO PEG-2','101114','GCC','56388-43-3, Mixture','1','disodium-oleamido-peg-2','QC: CLEAR LIGHT AMBER LIQUID',NULL,NULL,'SYN: STANDAPOL SH-100, UNIPOL SH-100, DISODIUM OLEAMIDO PEG-2 SULFOSUCCINATE AQUEOUS',NULL,'[null]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[null]',NULL,'[null]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8451,'DISODIUM PEG-5 LAURYLCITRATE SULFOSUCCINATE','101115','GCC','164780-83-0, Mixture','1','disodium-peg-5-laurylcitrate-sulfosuccinate','Clear yellow liquid with characteristic odor',NULL,'This mild anionic surfactant blend has good foam performance and improved thicken ability. Rewopol SB C 55- combines the superior mildness of a short chain capryl/capramidopropyl betaine with the higher concentrated and preservative-free sulfosuccinate. This synergistic combination can be used in a wide range of mild rinse-off formulations, e.g. baby or facial wash.','Disodium PEG-5 Laurylcitrate Sulfosuccinate; Unimate SBC; Rewopol SB C55','Store in a cool, dry, well-ventilated area away from incompatible substances. Keep containers tightly closed.','[\"100 ml. HDPE Bottle\",\"250 ml. HDPE Bottle\",\"200 kg. Poly Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[\"Solvents\",\"binders\",\"emulsifiers\",\"stabilizers\",\"foam & viscosity boosters\",\"thickeners\"]','N/A','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: N\\/A\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 S 2 CL 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: NO\",\"Molecular Weight: N\\/A\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33');
INSERT INTO `products` VALUES (8452,'DISODIUM UNDECYLENAMIDO MEA-SULFOSUCCINATE','101116','GCC','26650-05-5','1','disodium-undecylenamido-mea-sulfosuccinate','Light to yellow liquid with characteristic odor.','Mild surfactant recommended for application in anti-dandruff shampoos. Good skin compatibility.','Used in anti-dandruff shampoos, foam baths, foot shampoos, body shampoos, and shower shampoos.','Disodium Undecylenamido MEA-Sulfosuccinate; Unimate DMS; Rewocid SB U 185; Butanedioicacid, sulfo-, 4-[2-[(1-oxo-10-undecenyl)amino]ethyl] ester, disodium salt(9CI); Succinic acid, sulfo-, 4-ester with N-(2-hydroxyethyl)-10-undecenamide','Keep in sealed, unopened, original containers at 60ø – 80ø F. Avoid conditions of high humidity and temperature.','[\"250 ml. HDPE Bottle\",\"200 kg. Poly Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[\"Foam & viscosity boosters\",\"surfactants\"]','C17H28NNa2O8S','[\"Origin: Vegetable \\/ Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 1 year from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 S 2 CL 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 452.45 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8453,'DISTEAROYLETHYL DIMONIUM CHLORIDE','101117','GCC',NULL,'1','distearoylethyl-dimonium-chloride',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8454,'DISTEAROYLETHYL HYDROXYETHYLMONIUM METHOSULFATE (AND) CETEARYL ALCOHOL','101118','GCC','91032-11-0, Mixture','1','distearoylethyl-hydroxyethylmonium-methosulfate-an','QC: WHITE, YELLOWISH PEARLS WITH CHARACTERISTIC ODOR',NULL,NULL,'SYN: DEHYQUART F75',NULL,'[null]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[null]',NULL,'[null]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8455,'DISTEARYLDIMONIUM CHLORIDE','101119','GCC','107-64-2, 67-63-0','1','distearyldimonium-chloride','QC: OFF WHITE POWDER, AMINE-LIKE ODOR','Is a highly active conditioning agent and emulsifier for hair conditioners with an antistatic effect.',NULL,'SYN: VARISOFT TA-100',NULL,'[null]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[null]',NULL,'[null]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8456,'DISTEARYL PHTHALIC ACID AMIDE','101121','GCC','51365-71-0','1','distearyl-phthalic-acid-amide',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8457,'DISTILLATES (PETROLEUM), HYDROTREATED LIGHT','101122','GCC','64742-47-8','1','distillates-petroleum-hydrotreated-light',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8458,'DISTILLED DIACETYLATED MONOGLYCERIDE','101123','GCC','68990-54-5','1','distilled-diacetylated-monoglyceride','QC: CLEAR LIQUID',NULL,NULL,'SYN: QUEST INT’L TN: MYVACET 9-45 KOSHER, DISTILLED ACETYLATED MONOGLYCERIDES',NULL,'[null]','[\"Food & bev.\"]','[null]',NULL,'[null]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8459,'DL-ALANINE FCC','101124','GCC','74144-49-3','1','dl-alanine-fcc','Off-white powder',NULL,'DL-Alanine is used as nutrition supplement and seasoning in food processing industry. It can be used as a raw material for vitamin B6 synthesis and amaterial for the research on metabolism of amino acids by medical organisms or on a biochemical basis.dl-alanine could be used in pickles,drinks and wine.','DL-Alanine FCC; Upamine DA; ;(r,s)-alanine; Alanine, alpha; DL-ALA; FEMA 3818; Dl-Alanine,>99%','Store in cool place. Keep container tightly closed in a dry and well-ventilated place. Recommended storage temperature: 2 – 8 øC','[\"250 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"20 kg. Drum\",\"25 kg. Fiber Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Food & bev.\"]','[\"Nutritional supplements\",\"vitamins\"]','C13H14N2OHCl','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 226\\u00f8C\",\"Melting Point: 258-260 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 250.72 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8460,'DL-ALPHA-TOCOPHEROL USP, FCC [VITAMIN E ]','101125','GCC','10191-41-0','1','dl-alpha-tocopherol-usp-fcc-vitamin-e','Yellowish oily viscous liquid',NULL,'Is an efficient antioxidant, promotes wound healing, improved immune function and anti-aging','Dl-alpha-Tocopherol; 8-(4;ecyl)-;ephanyl;vitamin;Vitamin E; Unicoph T; 4-BroMo-2-(5;DL-Tocopherol)','Keep container tightly sealed between temperatures of 2-8øC.','[\"50 ml. Bottle\",\"20 kg. Pail\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Pharmaceutical\",\"Food & bev.\"]','[\"Preservatives\\/antimicrobial\",\"amino acid\",\"vitamins\"]','C29H50O2','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 73185 CLASS 60\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 240\\u00f8C (464\\u00f8F)\",\"Melting Point: 2.5-3.5 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 430.71 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8461,'D-LIMONENE','101126','GCC','5989-27-5','1','d-limonene','Colorless liquid with characteristic odor of lemons','Limonene is increasingly being used as a solvent for cleaning purposes, such as the removal of oil from machine parts, as it is produced from a renewable source (citrus oil, as a byproduct of orange juice manufacture). It is used as a paint stripper and is also useful as a fragrant alternative to turpentine. Limonene is also used as a solvent in some model airplane glues and as a constituent in some paints. All-natural commercial air fresheners, with air propellants, containing limonene are used by philatelists to remove self-adhesive postage stamps from envelope paper.','Limonene is common in cosmetic products. It is also used as a fragrance in perfumery, aftershave lotions, bath products and other such products that include fragrance. It is also used as botanical insecticide, the d enantiomer is most active as an insecticide. It is added to cleaning products such as hand cleansers to give a lemon-orange fragrance and because of its ability to dissolve oils. In natural and alternative medicine, d-limonene is marketed to relieve gastroesophageal reflux disease and heartburn.','D-Limonene; Unilene L; Cyclohexene, 1-methyl-4-(1-methylethenyl)-, (R)-; 4-Isopropenyl-1-methyl-1-cyclohexene;(R)-Limone; Limonene, (+)-','Keep container tightly sealed away from ignition sources.','[null]','[\"Cosmetics\",\"Industrial\"]','[\"Solvents\",\"acidulants\"]','C10H16','[\"Origin: Natural\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 50 \\u00f8C (122 \\u00f8F)\",\"Melting Point: -74.35 \\u00f8C (-101.83 \\u00f8F)\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 136.23 g\\/mol-1\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8462,'D-LIMONENE FOOD GRADE','101127','GCC','5989-27-5','1','d-limonene-food-grade','Colorless to pale yellow clear liquid with characteristic odor of lemons',NULL,'As the main odor constituent of citrus (plant family Rutaceae), d-limonene is used in food manufacturing and some medicines, e.g. as a flavoring to mask the bitter taste of alkaloids.','D-Limonene Food Grade; Unilene L-F; Cyclohexene, 1-methyl-4-(1-methylethenyl)-, (R)-; 4-Isopropenyl-1-methyl-1-cyclohexene;(R)-Limone; Limonene, (+)-','Keep container tightly sealed away from ignition sources.','[\"173 kg. Steel Drum\",\"390 lb. Steel Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[null]','[\"Solvents\",\"acidulants\"]','C10H16','[\"Origin: Natural\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 48580 SUB 3 CLASS 55\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 50 \\u00f8C (122 \\u00f8F)\",\"Melting Point: -74.35 \\u00f8C (-101.83 \\u00f8F)\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 136.23 g\\/mol-1\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8463,'D,L MALIC ACID FCC FINE GRANULAR KOSHER','101128','GCC','617-48-1','1','dl-malic-acid-fcc-fine-granular-kosher','White to off-white fine granular powder','The process of malolactic fermentation converts malic acid to much milder lactic acid. Malic acid occurs naturally in all fruits and many vegetables, and is generated in fruit metabolism.','Malic acid, when added to food products, is denoted by E number E296. Malic acid is the source of extreme tartness in USA-produced confectionery, the so-called extreme candy. It is also used with or in place of the less sour citric acid in sour sweets.','D,L Malic Acid FCC Fine GR KOS; Unacid MA; DL-Apfelsure; Hydroxy acid; DL-Apple Acid; Deoxytetraric Acid','Keep in a tightly closed container, stored in a cool, dry, ventilated area. Protect against physical damage.','[\"250 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"50 lb. Bag\",\"50 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"25 kg. Bag\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[\"Acidulants\"]','C4H6O5','[\"Origin: Natural\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 203\\u00f8C\",\"Melting Point: 131-133 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 134.09 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8464,'D,L MALIC ACID FCC GRANULAR KOSHER','101129','GCC','6915-15-7','1','dl-malic-acid-fcc-granular-kosher','White to nearly white crystals or granular powder','The process of malolactic fermentation converts malic acid to much milder lactic acid. Malic acid occurs naturally in all fruits and many vegetables, and is generated in fruit metabolism.','Malic acid, when added to food products, is denoted by E number E296. Malic acid is the source of extreme tartness in USA-produced confectionery, the so-called extreme candy. It is also used with or in place of the less sour citric acid in sour sweets.','Malic Acid FCC K; Unacid MA10; Deoxytetraric Acid; DL-Apfelsure; Hydroxy acid; DL-Apple Acid','Keep in a tightly closed container, stored in a cool, dry, ventilated area. Protect against physical damage.','[\"100 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"250 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"50 lb. Bag [TATE]\",\"50 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"25 kg. Bag [AS]\",\"25 kg. Fiber Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[null]','[\"Acidulants\"]','C4H6O5','[\"Origin: Natural\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 S 2 CL 85\",\"Kosher Status: Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 203\\u00f8C\",\"Melting Point: 131-133 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 134.09 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8465,'D,L MALIC ACID FCC SYNTHETIC KOSHER','101130','GCC','617-48-1','1','dl-malic-acid-fcc-synthetic-kosher','White or colorless crystalline powder','The process of malolactic fermentation converts malic acid to much milder lactic acid. Malic acid occurs naturally in all fruits and many vegetables, and is generated in fruit metabolism.','Malic acid, when added to food products, is denoted by E number E296. Malic acid is the source of extreme tartness in USA-produced confectionery, the so-called extreme candy. It is also used with or in place of the less sour citric acid in sour sweets.','D,L Malic Acid FCC SYN. K; Unacid MS20; Deoxytetraric Acid; DL-Apfelsure; Hydroxy acid; DL-Apple Acid','Keep in a tightly closed container, stored in a cool, dry, ventilated area. Protect against physical damage.','[\"50 lb. Bag\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Food & bev.\"]','[\"Acidulants\"]','C4H6O5','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 203\\u00f8C\",\"Melting Point: 131-133 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 134.09 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8466,'D,L MALIC ACID NF FCC SYNTHETIC KOSHER','101131','GCC','617-48-1','1','dl-malic-acid-nf-fcc-synthetic-kosher','White crystalline powder','The process of malolactic fermentation converts malic acid to much milder lactic acid. Malic acid occurs naturally in all fruits and many vegetables, and is generated in fruit metabolism.','Malic acid, when added to food products, is denoted by E number E296. Malic acid is the source of extreme tartness in USA-produced confectionery, the so-called extreme candy. It is also used with or in place of the less sour citric acid in sour sweets. Is also used in personal care, cosmetics, and pharmaceutical applications.','D,L Malic Acid NF FCC SYN K; Unacid MA30; Deoxytetraric Acid; DL-Apfelsure; Hydroxy acid; DL-Apple Acid','Keep in a tightly closed container, stored in a cool, dry, ventilated area. Protect against physical damage.','[\"100 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"250 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"5 lb. HDPE WM Bottle\",\"5 kg. Pail\",\"50 lb. Bag\",\"50 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"25 kg. Bag\",\"25 kg. Fiber Drum\",\"100 lb. Bag\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",null]','[\"Acidulants\"]','C4H6O5','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 203\\u00f8C\",\"Melting Point: 131-133 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 134.09 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8467,'DL-MANDELIC ACID 98%','101132','GCC','611-72-3','1','dl-mandelic-acid-98','White crystalline powder with faint odor',NULL,'Mandelic acid has a long history of use in the medical community as an antibacterial, particularly in the treatment of urinary tract infections. It has also been used as an oral antibiotic, and as a component of \'chemical face peels\', along with other alpha-hydroxy acids (AHAs). The drugs cyclandelate and homatropine are esters of mandelic acid.','DL-Mandelic Acid 98%; Upadel MA; 2-Hydroxy-2-Phenylacetic Acid; DL-Amygdalic Acid; DL-O-Hydroxyphenylacetic Acid; Phenylglycolic Acid','Do not store in direct sunlight. Store in a tightly closed container. Store in a cool, dry, well-ventilated area away from incompatible substances.','[\"100 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"1 kg. Bottle\",\"5 kg. HDPE OH Pail\",\"25 kg. Fiber Drum\",\"50 kg. Fiber Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Pharmaceutical\"]','[\"Acidulants\",\"emollient & esters\"]','C8H8O3','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 70 RV 2.15\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 162.6\\u00f8C\",\"Melting Point: 119-121 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 152.15 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8468,'DL-PANTHENOL 50% SOL\'N COSMETIC GRADE','101133','GCC','16485-10-2','1','dl-panthenol-50-soln-cosmetic-grade','White crystalline powder or light yellow liquid','Panthenol draws moisture from the atmosphere and readily binds to water molecules. When applied to the hair panthenol will help to moisturize it and give it a shine and gloss. For this reason it has become a very popular ingredient in shampoos and conditioners. In ointments, panthenol is an effective skin penetrator. It is sometimes mixed with allantoin, in concentrations of up to 2-5%, and is used for treatment of sunburns, mild burns and minor skin disorders. It improves hydration, reduces itching and inflammation of the skin, and accelerates epidermal wounds\' rate of healing.','In cosmetics and personal-care products, panthenol is a humectant, emollient, and moisturizer. It binds to the hair shaft readily; so, it is a common component of commercial shampoos and hair conditioners. It coats the hair and seals its surface, lubricating the hair shaft and giving it a shiny appearance. It is also recommended by many tattoo artists as a post-tattooing moisturising cream.','DL-Panthenol 50% Sol’N Coemstic Grade; T/N: Unithol PN50; T/N: DL-Panthenol 50 L; Pantenol; Pantenolo; Panthenolum; DL-Panthenol; ;(+/-)-Panthenol','Should be stored in a cool, dry, well-ventilated area in tightly sealed containers.','[\"250 ml. HDPE Bottle\",