in a similar manner to remove excess iron from the body.','EDTA Acid (Dissolvine); Universene Acid; Ethylenediaminetetraacetic Acid, Dissolvene Z-S; Edetic acid; 2,2′-{ethane-1,2-diylbis[(carboxymethyl)imino]}diacetate (non-preferred name); 3,4-diamino-3,4-bis(carboxymethyl)hexanedioic acid','Store in a tightly closed container away from direct sunlight. Store in a cool, dry, well-ventilated area away from incompatible substances.','[\"250 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"5 kg. HDPE OH Pail\",\"25 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"50 lb. Bag\",\"50 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Cosmetics\",\"industrial\",\"pharmaceutical\"]','[\"Acidulants\",\"chelating agents [sequestrants]\"]','C10H16N2O8','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC48581 S0 CL55\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 280.7\\u00f8C\",\"Melting Point: 250 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 292.24 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8505,'ELASTIN','101171','GCC','100085-10-7','1','elastin','Clear liquid',NULL,'Elastin is a highly elastic protein in connective tissue and allows many tissues in the body to resume their shape after stretching or contracting. Elastin helps skin to return to its original position when it is poked or pinched. Elastin is also an important load-bearing tissue in the bodies of vertebrates and used in places where mechanical energy is required to be stored.','Elastin; T/N: Elastin CLR; Unilast E; Elastine; Elastin from bovine neck ligament; Beta-Elastin; Elastin from human skin','No special instructions.','[\"50 ml. Bottle\",\"100 ml. Glass Bottle\",\"25 kg. Pail\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[null]','[\"Proteins\",\"amino acid\",\"emollient & esters\",\"emulsifiers\",\"moisturizer\"]','N/A','[\"Origin: Natural\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 18 \\u00f8C\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: NO\",\"Molecular Weight: N\\/A\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8506,'ELASTIN 10%, HYDROLYZED','101172','GCC','100085-10-7,7732-185','1','elastin-10-hydrolyzed',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8507,'EMULSIFYING WAX','101173','GCC','67762-27-0,9005-65-6','1','emulsifying-wax','White or pale yellow waxy solid with a low fatty alcohol odor',NULL,'Emulsifying wax is one of the essential ingredients in making lotions and creams. Lotions and creams are created from a mixture of water and oils. Without the addition of emulsifying wax, they too would separate back into water and oils.','Emulsifying Wax; Uniwax EW; Jeecol P; Emulsifying WAX P; Cetylstearyl Alcohol (and) Polysorbate 60','Store in a cool, dry, well ventilated place, in securely closed original container. Store away from sources of heat or ignition.','[\"250 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"5 kg. HDPE OH Pail\",\"50 lb. Bag\",\"50 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"25 kg. Box\",\"100 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"200 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[\"Emulsifiers\",\"waxes\",\"fatty alcohols\",\"fatty acids\"]','N/A','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC48580 S3 CL55\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: 123\\u00f8F\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: NO\",\"Molecular Weight: N\\/A\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8508,'EMULSION #8','101174','GCC','Unassigned','1','emulsion-8','Cloudy liquid','Examples of food emulsifiers are:\r\nEgg yolk ? in which the main emulsifying agent is lecithin. In fact, lecithos is the Greek word for egg yolk.\r\nMustard ? where a variety of chemicals in the mucilage surrounding the seed hull act as emulsifiers\r\nSoy lecithin is another emulsifier and thickener\r\nPickering stabilization ? uses particles under certain circumstances\r\nSodium stearoyl lactylate\r\nDATEM (Diacetyl Tartaric (Acid) Ester of Monoglyceride) ? an emulsifier used primarily in baking','Is a substance that stabilizes an emulsion by increasing its kinetic stability. One class of emulsifiers is known as \"surface active agents\", or surfactants.','Emulsion #8; Unisil 8','Store in a cool, dry, well ventilated place, in securely closed original container. Store away from sources of heat or ignition.','[\"420 lb. Steel Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Food & bev.\"]','[\"Emulsifiers\",\"surfactants\"]','N/A','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: N\\/A\",\"Freight Classification: N\\/A\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: NO\",\"Molecular Weight: N\\/A\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8509,'EMU OIL','101175','GCC','158570-96-8','1','emu-oil','White to off-white viscous oily liquid',NULL,'It can be used as a moisturizer and as a skin nourishing treatment. Emu Oil is a modern alternative method for helping relieve the discomfort of pain and inflammation caused by injured tissues and joints. Used for anti-aging effects, stretch marks & scars, arthritis, cuts & scrapes, burns, psoriasis & eczema, and in hair care.','Emu Oil; Unoil EMU; Ratite Oil; Emuoil, Kalayaoil; Emu Oil, Ultrapure','Store at room temperature in tightly sealed containers. Avoid external heat sources','[\"2 oz. HDPE Bottle\",\"100 ml. Glass Bottle\",\"7 lb. HDPE NM Jug\",\"39 lb. Pail\",\"55 Gallon Drum\"]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[\"Oils\",\"moisturizer\"]','N/A','[\"Origin: Natural\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 60000 CLASS 70 RV 2.15\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: >200\\u00f8F\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: N\\/A\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8510,'EPSOM SALT HEPTAHYDRATE USP','101176','GCC','10034-99-8','1','epsom-salt-heptahydrate-usp','White crystals',NULL,'Is a common pharmaceutical preparation of magnesium, commonly known as Epsom salt, used both externally and internally. Epsom salt is used as bath salts and for isolation tanks. Oral magnesium sulfate is commonly used as a saline laxative or osmotic purgative. Magnesium sulfate is the main preparation of intravenous magnesium.','Epsom Salt Heptahydrate USP; Magnesium Sulfate Heptahydrate (Epsom Salt); Uantox Esal; Unisalt E; Bettersalt; Bitter Salt; Magnesii Sulfas; Epsomite','Keep in a tightly closed container, store in a cool, dry, well-ventilated area.','[\"100 Gram Sample-China\",\"250 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"5 kg. Pail\",\"50 lb. Bag [GILES]\",\"50 lb. Bag\",\"50 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"25 kg. Bag\",\"100 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"50 kg. Fiber Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Pharmaceutical\"]','[\"Minerals\"]','MgO4S7H2O','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 1 year from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 S 2 CL 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: 1124 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 246.47 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8511,'ERGONOVINE MALEATE USP','101177','GCC','60-79-7','1','ergonovine-maleate-usp',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8512,'ERUCAMIDE','101178','GCC','112-84-5','1','erucamide','Beige flakes with a fatty odor',NULL,'13-Docosenamide is the amide of docosenoic acid. It was first identified in the cerebrospinal fluid of sleep-deprived cats. It has also been detected in the cerebrospinal fluid of rats and humans. 1 13-Docosenamide causes reduced mobility and slightly lessened awareness in rats, whereas 9-octadecenamide induces physiological sleep.','Erucamide; Cis-13-Docosenoic Amide; T/N: Erucylamide; Erucic Acid Amide; Kemamide E; Petrac Eramide; Polydis TR 131; Unislip 1753','Store in cool place. Keep container tightly closed in a dry and well-ventilated place.','[\"100 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Pharmaceutical\"]','[\"Acidulants\",\"fatty acids\"]','C22H43NO','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 1 year from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 230 \\u00f8C\",\"Melting Point: 79-81 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 337.58 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8513,'ERUCIC ACID 90%','101179','GCC','112-86-7','1','erucic-acid-90','White waxy solid or light yellow liquid at above 30oC',NULL,'Erucic acid has many of the same uses as mineral oils, but it is more readily biodegradable than some. It has limited ability to polymerize and dry for use in oil paints. Like other fatty acids, it can be converted into surfactants or lubricants, and can be used as a precursor to biodiesel fuel. Derivatives of erucic acid have many further uses, such as behenyl alcohol (CH3(CH2)21OH), a pour point depressant (enabling liquids to flow at a lower temperature), and silver behenate, for use in photography.','Erucic Acid 90%; Unicic A90; Unamide ER90; Nsc6814; Erucasàure; Erunic Acid; Prifrac 2990; Hystrene 2290; Docosenoic Acid','Keep container tightly closed in a dry and well-ventilated place.','[\"250 ml. HDPE Bottle\",\"35 lb. Blue TH Pail\",\"180 kg. Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Industrial\"]','[\"Acidulants\",\"fatty acids\",\"minerals\",\"oils\"]','C22H42O2','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: N\\/A\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 113 \\u00f8C (235 \\u00f8F) - closed cup\",\"Melting Point: 33 - 35 \\u00f8C (91 - 95 \\u00f8F)\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 338.57 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8514,'ERYTHORBIC ACID FCC K PDR','101180','GCC','89-65-6','1','erythorbic-acid-fcc-k-pdr','White to yellow crystalline or granular solid',NULL,'Is a food preservative that is a strong reducing agent (oxygen accepting) which functions similarly to antioxidants. It is used in meat curing to speed and control the nitrite curing reaction and prolong the color of cured meat at levels of 0.05%.','Erythorbic Acid FCC K PDR; Erythorbic Acid FCC; Uantox EBATE; 2,3-didehydro-d-erythro-hexono-1,4-lactone; Erycorbin; Saccharosonic Acid; D(-)-Isoascorbic Acid','Keep container tightly closed when not in use. Store containers in a cool, dry location, away from direct sunlight, sources of intense heat, or where freezing is possible.','[\"250 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"1 kg. HDPE WM Bottle\",\"5 lb. HDPE WM Bottle\",\"5 kg. HDPE OH Pail\",\"25 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"50 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"25 kg. Fiber Drum\",\"25 kg. Box\",\"100 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"110 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"220 lb. Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Food & bev.\"]','[\"Preservatives\\/antimicrobials\"]','C6H8O6','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: 169-172 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 176.12 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8515,'ERYTHRULOSE','101181','GCC','496-55-9','1','erythrulose','Clear to pale yellowish liquid',NULL,'It is used in some self-tanning cosmetics, in general, combined with dihydroxyacetone (DHA).','Erythrulose; Unilose ERY; D-Glycerotetrulose; D-Threulose; D-glycero-2-Tetrulose; (3R)-1,3,4-Trihydroxy-2-butanone','Store in a cool, dry, well-ventilated area between temperatures of 2oC and 8oC.','[\"50 ml. Bottle\",\"1 kg. Bottle\",\"10 kg. Open HD Pail\"]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[\"Chemicals general\"]','C4H8O4','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date when properly stored\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 60000 CLASS 70 RV 2.15\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 179.4 \\u00f8C\",\"Melting Point: 198-201 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 120.104 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8516,'ESTER GUM PASTILLE','101182','GCC','8050-30-4','1','ester-gum-pastille','Pale yellow to colorless liquid','Is used as a solubilizer and cross-linking agent in polymer chemistry for: proteins (leather tanning process), collagen, cellulose derivatives (textiles), hydrocolloids, and starch (paper coatings).','Coated paper and textile finishes use large amounts of glyoxal as a crosslinker for starch-based formulations. It condenses with urea to afford 4,5-dihydroxy-2-imidazolidinone, which further reacts with formaldehyde to give the bis(hydroxymethyl) derivative used for wrinkle-resistant chemical treatments.','Glyoxal 40%; Ethanedial; Bisformyl; Glyoxylaldehyde; Glyoxal Solution; Diformyl; Ethanedial; 1,2-ethanedione;Oxalaldehyde; Unox G40','Keep container tightly closed in a dry and well-ventilated place. Containers which are opened must be carefully resealed and kept upright to prevent leakage. Recommended storage temperature 2 – 8 øC','[\"250 ml. HDPE Bottle\",\"551 lb. Poly Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Pharmaceutical\",\"Industrial\"]','[\"Acs\\/reagent\"]','C2H2O2','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 6 months from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: -4 \\u00f8C (25 \\u00f8F)\",\"Melting Point: 15 \\u00f8C (59 \\u00f8F)\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 58.04 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8517,'ETHANEDIAL, OXALALDEHYDE','101183','GCC','107-22-2, 7732-18-5','1','ethanedial-oxalaldehyde','Pale yellow to colorless liquid','Is used as a solubilizer and cross-linking agent in polymer chemistry for: proteins (leather tanning process), collagen, cellulose derivatives (textiles), hydrocolloids, and starch (paper coatings).','Coated paper and textile finishes use large amounts of glyoxal as a crosslinker for starch-based formulations. It condenses with urea to afford 4,5-dihydroxy-2-imidazolidinone, which further reacts with formaldehyde to give the bis(hydroxymethyl) derivative used for wrinkle-resistant chemical treatments.','Glyoxal 40%; Ethanedial; Bisformyl; Glyoxylaldehyde; Glyoxal Solution; Diformyl; Ethanedial; 1,2-ethanedione;Oxalaldehyde; Unox G40','Keep container tightly closed in a dry and well-ventilated place. Containers which are opened must be carefully resealed and kept upright to prevent leakage. Recommended storage temperature 2 – 8 øC','[\"250 ml. HDPE Bottle\",\"551 lb. Poly Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Pharmaceutical\",\"Industrial\"]','[\"Acs\\/reagent\"]','C2H2O2','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 6 months from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: -4 \\u00f8C (25 \\u00f8F)\",\"Melting Point: 15 \\u00f8C (59 \\u00f8F)\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 58.04 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8518,'ETHER, REAGENT, A.C.S','101184','GCC','60-29-7','1','ether-reagent-acs','Clear colorless liquid',NULL,'Diethyl ether has a high cetane number of 85-96 and is used as a starting fluid, in combination with petroleum distillates for gasoline and diesel engines because of its high volatility and low flash point. Diethyl ether is a common laboratory solvent.','Ether; Ether; Aether; (C2H5)2O; Pronarcol; Aether DAB; Ether,Ethyl; Ethyl Ether; Uether E','Keep in a flammables area away from heat, sparks, flame, and all sources of ignition. Keep in a tightly closed container. Store in a cool, dry, well-ventilated area away from incompatible substances. Store protected from light under an inert atmosphere. Keep away from oxidizing agents.','[\"4 l. PVC Gl Bottle\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[null]','[\"Acs\\/reagent\"]','C4H10O','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 1 year from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: -40 \\u00f8F\",\"Melting Point: -116 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 74.12 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8519,'ETHER USP','101185','GCC','60-29-7','1','ether-usp','Clear colorless liquid',NULL,'The anesthetic effects of ether have made it a recreational drug. Diethyl ether in anesthetic dosage is an inhalant which has a long history of recreational use. One disadvantage is the high flammability, especially in conjunction with oxygen.','Ether USP; Ether; Aether; (C2H5)2O; Pronarcol; Aether DAB; Ether,Ethyl; Ethyl Ether; Uether E','Keep in a flammables area away from heat, sparks, flame, and all sources of ignition. Keep in a tightly closed container. Store in a cool, dry, well-ventilated area away from incompatible substances. Store protected from light under an inert atmosphere. Keep away from oxidizing agents.','[\"4 l. PVC Gl Bottle\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Pharmaceutical\"]','[\"Solvents\"]','C4H10O','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 1 year from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: -40 \\u00f8F\",\"Melting Point: -116 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 74.12 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8520,'ETHOXYDIGLYCOL [DEITHYLENE GLYCOL MONOETHER]','101186','GCC','111-90-0','1','ethoxydiglycol-deithylene-glycol-monoether','Clear colorless liquid with slight odor',NULL,'In cosmetics and personal care products, these ingredients are used in the formulation of hair and bath products, eye and facial makeup, fragrances, personal cleanliness products, and shaving and skin care products. Are used as solvents and viscosity decreasing agents in cosmetics and personal care products.','Ethoxydiglycol; Diethylene Glycol Monoethyl Ether; Trivalin SF; Unisept EDG; 2-(2-ethoxyethoxy)ethanol; Transcutol; Carbitol Solvent; Dioxitol','Store in a cool, dry place. Keep away from heat and flame.','[\"250 ml. HDPE Bottle\",\"20 kg. Pail\",\"441 lb. Drum\",\"441 lb. Poly Drum\",\"442 lb. Poly Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[\"Solvents\"]','C6H14O3','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 3 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 S 2 CL 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 96\\u00f8C (204.8\\u00f8F)\",\"Melting Point: -76 \\u00f8C (-105 \\u00f8F)\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 134.17 g\\/mol-1\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8521,'ETHOXYLATED COCOAMINE (LATEX STABILIZER)','101187','GCC','61791-14-8','1','ethoxylated-cocoamine-latex-stabilizer','QC: CLEAR, SLIGHT YELLOW LIQUID WITH AMINE ODOR',NULL,NULL,'SYN: VARONIC K 202',NULL,'[null]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[null]',NULL,'[null]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8522,'ETHOXYLATED LANOLIN','101189','GCC','61790-81-6','1','ethoxylated-lanolin','QC: PALE YELLOW TO AMBER VISCOUS LIQUID',NULL,NULL,'SYN: SOLULAN L-575, LUBRIZOL T/N: PEG-75 LANOLIN, Polyoxyethylene 75 Lanolin',NULL,'[null]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[null]',NULL,'[null]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8523,'ETHOXYLATED METHYL GLUCOSIDE DIOLEATE','101191','GCC','86893-19-8','1','ethoxylated-methyl-glucoside-dioleate','QC: SLIGHTLY YELLOW WAXY BEADS',NULL,NULL,'SYN: ANTIL 120, PEG-120 METHYL GLUCOSE DIOLEATE',NULL,'[null]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[null]',NULL,'[null]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8524,'ETHOXYLATED NONYLPHENOL','101192','GCC','Mixture','1','ethoxylated-nonylphenol','Light yellow viscous liquid with phenolic smell',NULL,'Nonylphenol is used in manufacturing antioxidants, lubricating oil additives, laundry and dish detergents, emulsifiers, and solubilizers. It can also be used to produce tris(4-nonyl-phenyl) phosphite (TNPP), which is an antioxidant used to protect polymers, such as rubber, vinyl, polyolefins, and polystyrenics in addition to being a stabilizer in plastic food packaging. Barium and calcium salts of nonylphenol are also used as heat stabilizers for polyvinyl chloride (PVC). Nonylphenol is also often used an intermediate in the manufacture of the non-ionic surfactants nonylphenol exthoxylates, which are used in detergents, paints, pesticides, personal care products, and plastics. Nonylphenol and nonylphenol ethoxylates are only used as components of household detergents outside of Europe.','Ethoxylated Nonylphenol; Triton N- 101; Uniton N 101; Polyethylene Mono(nonylphenyl)ether Glycols; Nonylphenyl Polyethyleneglycol Ether, Nonionic; Macrogol Nonylphenyl Ether; POE Nonyl Phenyl Ether','Recommended storage temperature for these products is within a range 10 to 35oC.','[\"480 lb. Steel Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Industrial\"]','[\"Emulsifiers\",\"antioxidants\",\"oils\",\"stabilizer\",\"surfactants\"]','C15H24O','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC48580 S3 CL55\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: >140 \\u00f8 F\",\"Melting Point: -8 to 2 \\u00f8C (18-36 \\u00f8F)\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 220.35 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8525,'ETHOXYLATED NONYLPHENOL, BRANCHED','101193','GCC','9016-45-9','1','ethoxylated-nonylphenol-branched','Slightly hazy, light amber liquid',NULL,'IGEPAL CO-630 is a nonionic co-emulsifier used in emulsion polymerization and also widely used as a wetting agent in different formulations. Product applications include: Pulp & Paper, Plastics, Textiles, Mining, Paints & Coatings, Lubrication, I&I Surface Cleaning, Laundry, and Hard Surface Cleaners.','Igepal CO630; Unipal CO630; Ethoxylated Nonphenol, Branched; Octoxynol 9; 2-[2-(4-Nonylphenoxy)Ethoxy]Ethanol; Lissapol; Ethoxylated Alkyl Phenol; NP-40 Alternative','Keep in tightly closed container. Keep in a cool, dry, well-ventilated area.','[\"250 ml. HDPE Bottle\",\"40 lb. Blue OH Pail\",\"475 lb. Liquipak\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Cosmetics\",\"Industrial\"]','[\"Emulsifiers\"]','C15H24O(C2H4O)n','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC48580 S3 CL55\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 535 \\u00f8F\",\"Melting Point: 44-46 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 308.45 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8526,'ETHOXYQUIN FOOD GRADE','101194','GCC','91-53-2','1','ethoxyquin-food-grade','Yellow liquid',NULL,'An antioxidant used in the preservation of color in chili powder, ground chili, and paprika. Is a fat preservative sometimes used in dog food.','Ethoxyquin Food Grade; Unichem EQ; antageaw; AntioxidantAW; Antioxidantec; 1,2-Dihydro-6-Ethoxy-2,2,4-Trimethylquinoline; Raluquin-; Santoquin; Stop-Scald','Store in tightly sealed containers. Keep in a cool, dry area.','[\"452 lb. Steel Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Food & bev.\"]','[\"Antioxidants\",\"preservatives.naturals\"]','C14H19NO','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: N\\/A\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 137 \\u00f8C\",\"Melting Point: <0\\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 217.31 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:55','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(8527,'ETHYL ACETATE 99% FCC NF','101195','GCC','141-78-6','1','ethyl-acetate-99-fcc-nf','Clear colorless liquid with strong fruity odor',NULL,'Ethyl acetate is used primarily as a solvent and diluent, being favored because of its low cost, low toxicity, and agreeable odor. For example, it is commonly used to clean circuit boards and in some nail varnish removers (acetone and acetonitrile are also used). Coffee beans and tea leaves are decaffeinated with this solvent. It is also used in paints as an activator or hardener.','Ethyl Acetate 99% FCC NF; Unisept EA9; Unetate EA99; Acetic Acid; Ethyl Ester; Acetic Ether; Acetidin; Acetoxyethane; Ethyl Acetic Ester; Ethyl Ethanoate; Vinegar Naphtha; Ac