/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: N\\/A\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:56','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(9180,'METHYLBROMIDE HOMATROPINE','101974','GCC','80-49-9','1','methylbromide-homatropine','White powder',NULL,'Homatropine methylbromide is a quaternary ammonium muscarinic acetylcholine receptor antagonist belonging to the group of medicines called anti-muscarinics. Homatropine is used to treat duodenal or stomach ulcers or intestine problems. It can be used together with antacids or other medicine in the treatment of peptic ulcer. It may also be used to prevent nausea, vomiting, and motion sickness.','Methyl Bromide Homatropine; 1aH,5aH-Tropanium, 3a-hydroxy-8-methyl-, bromide, mandelate (8CI); 8-Methylhomatropinium bromide(6CI,7CI); Camatropine','Store in a cool, dry, well-ventilated area away from light.','[\"1 kg. Bottle\"]','[\"Pharmaceutical\"]','[\"Quaternary compounds\"]','C17H24BrNO3','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 197.7\\u00f8C\",\"Melting Point: 192\\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 370.28 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:56','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(9181,'METHYL CARBITOL SOLVENT','101975','GCC','111-77-3','1','methyl-carbitol-solvent','Colorless liquid with characteristic odor',NULL,'Methyl Carbitol- glycol ether is a very hydrophilic, slow-evaporating glycol ether. Its primary use is as a de-icing additive for aviation fuel. Methyl Carbitol- glycol ether can also be used in coalescing blends with other solvents where high polymer solvency and tailing activities are needed.','Methyl Carbitol Solvnt; Diethylene Glycol Monomethyl Ether; DM; 3,6-Dioxaheptan-1-ol; Methoxydiglyc0l; Digylcol Monomethyl Ether','Keep container tightly closed. Store away from heat and light.','[\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Industrial\"]','[\"Solvents\"]','C5H12O3','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 1 year from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC48580 S3 CL55\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 183 \\u00f8F\",\"Melting Point: -70 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 120.15 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:56','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(9182,'METHYL CELLULOSE 4000 CPS','101976','GCC','9004-67-5','1','methyl-cellulose-4000-cps','White to off-white powder',NULL,'Methyl cellulose is very occasionally added to hair shampoos, tooth pastes and liquid soaps, to generate their characteristic thick consistency. This is also done for foods, for example ice cream or croquette. Methyl cellulose is also an important emulsifier, preventing the separation of two mixed liquids because it is an emulsion stabilizer. Methyl cellulose is used as a variable viscosity personal lubricant; it is the main ingredient in K-Y Jelly. Methyl cellulose is used in the manufacture of capsules in nutritional supplements, its edible and nontoxic properties provide a vegetarian alternative to the use of gelatin. Methyl cellulose finds a major application as a performance additive in construction materials.','Methyl Cellulose 4000 CPS; Methyl Cellulose MCA 4M; Unocel 40; Nicel; Tylose; Viscol; Bagolax; Adulsin; Cologel; Edisolm','Keep container tightly closed in a dry and well-ventilated place.','[\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Pharmaceutical\",\"Industrial\",\"Food & bev.\",\"Cosmetics\"]','[\"Buffering agents\",\"binders\",\"nutritional supplments\",\"stabilizer\"]','C12H20O10','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: N\\/A\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 196.3\\u00f8C\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 324.28 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:56','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(9183,'METHYL CELLULOSE MCA 4M 4000 CPS','101977','GCC','9004-67-5','1','methyl-cellulose-mca-4m-4000-cps','White to off-white powder',NULL,'Methyl cellulose is very occasionally added to hair shampoos, tooth pastes and liquid soaps, to generate their characteristic thick consistency. This is also done for foods, for example ice cream or croquette. Methyl cellulose is also an important emulsifier, preventing the separation of two mixed liquids because it is an emulsion stabilizer. Methyl cellulose is used as a variable viscosity personal lubricant; it is the main ingredient in K-Y Jelly. Methyl cellulose is used in the manufacture of capsules in nutritional supplements, its edible and nontoxic properties provide a vegetarian alternative to the use of gelatin. Methyl cellulose finds a major application as a performance additive in construction materials.','Methyl Cellulose MCA 4M; Demacol MCA 4M; Methyl Cellulose; Unocel 40; Nicel; Tylose; Viscol; Bagolax; Adulsin; Cologel; Edisolm',NULL,'[\"23 kg. Box\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Pharmaceutical\",\"Industrial\",\"Food & bev.\",\"Cosmetics\"]','[\"Buffering agents\",\"binders\",\"nutritional supplments\",\"stabilizer\"]','C12H20O10','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 196.3\\u00f8C\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 324.28 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:56','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(9184,'METHYLCOBALAMIN','101978','GCC','13422-55-4','1','methylcobalamin','Dark red crystalline powder','A lack of methylcobalamin can lead to megaloblastic anemia and subacute combined degeneration of the spinal cord.','This vitamer is one of two active coenzymes used by vitamin B12-dependent enzymes and is the specific vitamin B12 form used by 5-methyltetrahydrofolate-homocysteine methyltransferase (MTR), also known as methionine synthase.','Methylcobalamin; MeCbl; Algobaz; methyl-b12; Vitamin B12; Hitocobamin-M','Store in cool place. Keep container tightly closed in a dry and well-ventilated place.','[\"5 Gram Poly Bag\",\"250 Gram H