lets; Unichem SOHYA; Lye; Caustic soda; Sodium hydrate; Soda lye','Store in a tightly closed container. Store in a cool, dry, well-ventilated area away from incompatible substances. Keep away from metals.','[\"250 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"50 kg. Fiber Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Industrial\"]','[\"Acs\\/reagent\",\"absorptions bases\"]','NaOH','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 3 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 46230,SUB 3\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Melting Point: 9-10 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 39.99 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:57','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10120,'SODIUM HYDROXIDE NF/FCC PELLET','103099','GCC','1310-73-2','1','sodium-hydroxide-nffcc-pellet','White pellets','One of its many characteristics is that it\'s a deliquescent alkali and absorbs carbon dioxide and moisture from the air. Food grade sodium hydroxide is used in the chemical washing and peeling of fruits and vegetables, softening of firm substances and as a thickening agent.','The dissolution of solid sodium hydroxide in water creates a highly exothermic reaction (creates a lot of heat). One of its many characteristics is that it\'s a deliquescent alkali and absorbs carbon dioxide and moisture from the air. Used in many industries, most notably in the manufacture of pulp, paper, textiles, drinking water, detergents and as a pharmaceutical excipient.','Sodium Hydroxide NF/FCC Pellet; Unichem SOHYD; Lye; Caustic soda; Sodium hydrate; Soda lye','Store in a tightly closed container. Store in a cool, dry, well-ventilated area away from incompatible substances. Keep away from metals.','[\"250 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"5 lb. HDPE WM Bottle\",\"5 kg. HDPE OH Pail\",\"25 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"25 kg. Pail\",\"50 kg. FDRM- Kosher\",\"110 lb. Drum [MALLK]\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Pharmaceutical\",\"industrial\",\"food & bev.\"]','[\"Excipients\",\"thickener\",\"absorptions bases\"]','NaOH','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 3 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 46230 SUB 3 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: 9-10 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 39.99 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:57','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10121,'SODIUM HYDROXIDE REAGENT GRADE','103100','GCC','1310-73-2','1','sodium-hydroxide-reagent-grade','White crystalline or flake',NULL,'Its chemical specifications are the de facto standards for chemicals used in many high-purity applications and typically designate the highest quality chemical available for laboratory use.','Sodium Hydroxide Reagent Grade; Unichem SOHYR; Lye; Caustic soda; Sodium hydrate; Soda lye','Store in a tightly closed container. Store in a cool, dry, well-ventilated area away from incompatible substances. Keep away from metals.','[\"250 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"5 kg. HDPE OH Pail\",\"50 lb. Bag\",\"50 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"100 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Pharmaceutical\"]','[\"Acs\\/reagent\"]','NaOH','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 3 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 46230,SUB 3\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: 9-10 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 39.99 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:57','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10122,'SODIUM HYDROXYMETHYLGLYCINATE','103101','GCC','70161-44-3','1','sodium-hydroxymethylglycinate','Colorless to light yellow transparent liquid',NULL,'Suttocide A is derived from the naturally-occurring amino acid Glycine. A single preservative, Suttocide A is a broad-spectrum antimicrobial active against Gram-negative, Gram-Positive bacteria, yeast and molds. It has good anti-bacterial and anti-mold properties, but its weakest against yeast. Its antifungal and anti-mold activity is increased with a higher usage rate. It is used in personal care products.','Sodium Hydroxymethyl Glycinate; Suttocide A 50% Solution; Sodium Hydroxymethylamino Acetate; Sodium 2-((hydroxymethyl)amino)acetate','Keep containers tightly closed when not in use. Store in a cool, dry place, out of direct sunlight.','[\"100 ml. HDPE Bottle\",\"250 ml. HDPE Bottle\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[\"Preservatives\\/antimicrobial\",\"amino acid\",\"emulsifiers\"]','C3H6NNaO3','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: N\\/A\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 S 2 CL 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 139.6 \\u00f8C\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 127.07 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:57','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10123,'SODIUM HYPOCHLORITE 12.5% SOL','103102','GCC','7681-52-9, 1310-73-2','1','sodium-hypochlorite-125-sol','Water clear to a slight greenish-yellow, or light yellow aqueous solution',NULL,'Is another name for liquid bleach which is used as a disinfectant and oxidizing agent.','Sodiuim Hypochlorite 12.5% Soultion; Sodium Hypochlorite 15% Solution; T/N: Unite Hype 15; Liquid Bleach','Store in a cool, dry area away from direct sunlight and heat to avoid deterioration.','[\"5 Gallon Pail\",\"12 Gallon Poly Carboy\",\"50 Gallon Poly Drum\",\"55 Gallon Poly Drum\",\"500 lb. Poly Drum\",\"1 Gallon Bulk\"]','[\"Industrial\"]','[\"Surfactants\"]','NaOCI','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: N\\/A\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 48580 SUB 3 CLASS 55\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: -16 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 74.5 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:57','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10124,'SODIUM HYPOCHLORITE 5% SOL USP','103103','GCC','7681-52-9','1','sodium-hypochlorite-5-sol-usp','Clear light yellow green liquid',NULL,'Dilute bleach baths have been used for decades to treat moderate to severe eczema in humans.','Sodium Hypochlorite 5% Solution USP; Unite HYP5; Antiformin; Carrel-Dakin solution; Surgical chlorinated soda solution','Store in a cool