 is sanitary, dry, well-ventilated, cool, isolated from all toxic and harmful substances, away from ignition sources.','[\"100 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"250 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"50 lb. Bag\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Food & bev.\"]','[\"Buffering agents\",\"emulsifier\",\"thickener\",\"phosphates\"]','Na4O7P2','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 S 2 CL 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: 80 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 265.90 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10481,'TETRASODIUM PYROPHOS AH FCC GR','103555','GCC','7722-88-5','1','tetrasodium-pyrophos-ah-fcc-gr','White granular',NULL,'Tetrasodium pyrophosphate is used as a buffering agent, an emulsifier, a dispersing agent, and a thickening agent, and is often used as a food additive. Common foods containing tetrasodium pyrophosphate include chicken nuggets, marshmallows, pudding, crab meat, imitation crab, canned tuna, and soy-based meat alternatives and cat foods and cat treats where it is used as a palatability enhancer.','Tetrasodium Pyrophosphate AH FCC Ganular; TSPP; Pyrophosphoric acid, tetrasodiumsalt; Sodium Diphosphate','Store in a tightly closed container. Store in an area that is sanitary, dry, well-ventilated, cool, isolated from all toxic and harmful substances, away from ignition','[\"250 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"50 lb. Bag\",\"100 lb. Bag\",\"100 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Food & bev.\"]','[\"Buffering agents\",\"emulsifier\",\"thickener\",\"phosphates\"]','Na4O7P2','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 S 2 CL 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: 80 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 265.90 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10482,'TETRASODIUM PYROPHOS AH FCC PD','103556','GCC','7722-88-5','1','tetrasodium-pyrophos-ah-fcc-pd','White powder',NULL,'Tetrasodium pyrophosphate is used as a buffering agent, an emulsifier, a dispersing agent, and a thickening agent, and is often used as a food additive. Common foods containing tetrasodium pyrophosphate include chicken nuggets, marshmallows, pudding, crab meat, imitation crab, canned tuna, and soy-based meat alternatives and cat foods and cat treats where it is used as a palatability enhancer.','Tetrasodium Pyrophosphate AH FCC Powder; TSPP; Pyrophosphoric acid, tetrasodiumsalt; Sodium Diphosphate','Store in a tightly closed container. Store in an area that is sanitary, dry, well-ventilated, cool, isolated from all toxic and harmful substances, away from ignition sources.','[\"100 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"250 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Food & bev.\"]','[\"Buffering agents\",\"emulsifier\",\"thickener\",\"phosphates\"]','Na4O7P2','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 S 2 CL 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: 80 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 265.90 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10483,'TETRASODIUM PYROPHOS AH P TECH','103557','GCC','7722-88-5','1','tetrasodium-pyrophos-ah-p-tech','White powder','In toothpaste and dental floss, tetrasodium pyrophosphate acts as a tartar control agent, serving to remove calcium and magnesium from saliva and thus preventing them from being deposited on teeth. Tetrasodium pyrophosphate is used in commercial dental rinses before brushing to aid in plaque reduction.','Tetrasodium pyrophosphate is sometimes used in household detergents to prevent similar deposition on clothing, but due to its phosphate content it causes eutrophication of water, promoting algae growth.','Tetrasodium Pyrophosphate AH P Tech Grade; TSPP; Pyrophosphoric acid, tetrasodiumsalt; Sodium Diphosphate','Store in a tightly closed container. Store in an area that is sanitary, dry, well-ventilated, cool, isolated from all toxic and harmful substances, away from ignition sources.','[\"250 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"50 lb. Screw T Pail\",\"55 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Industrial\",\"cosmetics\"]','[\"Phosphates\"]','Na4O7P2','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 48580 SUB 3 CLASS 55\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: 80 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 265.90 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10484,'TETRASODIUM PYROPHOS DECAHYD','103558','GCC','13472-36-1','1','tetrasodium-pyrophos-decahyd','White crystals',NULL,'Sodium pyrophosphate decahydrate, also called tetrabasic pyrophosphate or TSPP is used in the laboratory as a buffering agent. The compound has been shown to be useful in the preparation of an EDTA-sodium pyrophosphate extraction buffer for microcystin analysis of soil samples.','Tetrasodium Pyrophosphate Decahydrate FCC; Sodium pyrophosphate tetrabasic decahydrate; Tetrasodium pyrophosphate; TSPP','Store in a tightly closed container. Store in an area that is sanitary, dry, well-ventilated, cool, isolated from all toxic and harmful substances, away from ignition sources.','[\"100 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Industrial\"]','[\"Buffering agents\"]','H20Na4O17P2','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 48580 SUB 3 CLASS 55\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: 80 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 446.06 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10485,'TETRASODIUM PYROPHOS FCC AH PW','103559','GCC','7722-88-5','1','tetrasodium-pyrophos-fcc-ah-pw','White powder',NULL,'Tetrasodium pyrophosphate is used as a buffering agent, an emulsifier,