g Point: 250 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 337.27 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10491,'THIMEROSAL USP BP','103565','GCC','54-64-8','1','thimerosal-usp-bp','White to off-white crystalline powder',NULL,'It is an organomercury compound commonly used for its anticeptic and antifungal capabilities. Its most common uses are in the medical applications of skin test antigens, drug preservatives, antivenins, and opthalmic and nasal products.','Thimerosal USP BP; Umerasol T; Ethylmercurithiosalicylic Acid Sodium Salt; Sodium (2-Carboxyphenylthio)ethylmercury','Keep container tightly closed in a dry and well-ventilated place. Store away from incompatible materials. Protect from light.','[\"1 kg. Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Pharmaceutical\"]','[\"Preservatives\\/antimicrobials\",\"chemicals general\"]','C9H9HgNaO2S','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: N\\/A\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 250\\u00f8C (449.6\\u00f8F)\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 404.81 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10492,'THIOGLYCOLIC ACID 80%','103566','GCC','68-11-1','1','thioglycolic-acid-80','Clear colorless liquid with a strong unpleaseant odor',NULL,'TGA is the precursor to ammonium thioglycolate that is used for permanents. TGA and its derivatives break the disulfide bonds in the cortex of hair. One reforms these broken bonds in giving hair a \"perm.\" Applying TGA can soften nails and then fix pincer nails in the correct position.','Thiglycolic Acid 80%; 2-Sulfanylacetic acid; Acetyl mercaptan; Thiovanic acid; Mercaptoacetic acid','Keep away from heat. When not in use, tightly seal the container and store in a dry, cool place.','[\"250 ml. Amber Bottle\",\"540 lb. Poly Drum\",\"550 lb. Poly Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[\"Chemicals general\"]','C2H4O2S','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 126 \\u00f8C\",\"Melting Point: -16 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 92.12 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10493,'THIOSALICYLIC ACID','103567','GCC','147-93-3','1','thiosalicylic-acid','Light yellow crystalline powder',NULL,'Thiosalicylic acid is a precursor to the dyestuff thioindigo. Thiosalicylic acid is also used to make the vaccine preservative thiomersal. It is a precursor to drug candidates for treatment of atherosclerosis and melanoma.','Thiosalicylic Acid; Unacid THS; 2-Mercaptobenzoic acid; o-Thiosalicylic acid; 2-Sulfanylbenzoic acid','Store in cool, well-ventilated area. Keep container tightly closed. It is air and light sensitive. Store under Argon.','[\"50 kg. Fiber Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Industrial\",\"pharmaceutical\"]','[\"Chemicals general\"]','C7H6O2S','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: N\\/A\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 150 \\u00f8C\",\"Melting Point: 162-165 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 154.19 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10494,'THIOUREA 99%','103568','GCC','Thiourea, 62-56-6','1','thiourea-99','White crystals or powder',NULL,'The main application of thiourea is in textile processing. Thiourea is commonly employed as a source of sulfide, e.g. for converting alkyl halides to thiols. Thioureas are used a building blocks to pyrimidine derivatives. Other industrial uses of thiourea include production of flame retardant resins, and vulcanization accelerators. Thiourea is used as an auxiliary agent in diazo paper, light-sensitive photocopy paper and almost all other types of copy paper. It is also used to tone silver-gelatin photographic prints.','Thiourea 99%; Thiourea; Unirea 99%; Thiocarbamide','Keep container closed when not in use. Store in a tightly closed container. Store in a cool, dry, well-ventilated area away from incompatible substances.','[\"250 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"35 lb. Pail\",\"50 lb. Bag\",\"51 lb. Bag\",\"25 kg. Bag\",\"25 kg. Fiber Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Industrial\"]','[\"Chemicals general\"]','CH4N2S','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: 182 \\u00f8C (360 \\u00f8F)\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 76.12 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10495,'THIOUREA ACS REAGENT','103569','GCC','Thiourea, 62-56-6','1','thiourea-acs-reagent','White powder',NULL,'Thiourea is a chaotropic agent or strong denaturant. It has been used to solubilize membrane and organelle specific proteins for analysis by two-dimensional gel electrophoresis. Thiourea is a free radical scavenger of the peroxide radical. It was shown to inhibit lipid peroxidation and UV-induced crosslinking of collagen. As a chelator of cuprous copper, thiourea inhibits this intermediate in oxidative reactions of cupric ion.','Thiourea ACS Reagent; Unirea 99R; Thiourea 99%; Thiourea; Thiocarbamide','Keep container closed when not in use. Store in a tightly closed container. Store in a cool, dry, well-ventilated area away from incompatible substances.','[\"12 kg. HDPE WM Bottle\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Pharmaceutical\"]','[\"Acs\\/reagent\",\"chelating agent [sequestrants]\"]','CH4N2S','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: 182 \\u00f8C (360 \\u00f8F)\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 76.12 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10496,'THYME OIL RED','103570','GCC','8007-46-3','1','thyme-oil-red','Amber to orange red clear liquid',NULL,'It is widely used in botanical therapy since antiquity for its warming, stimulating, and cleansing properties, it is also considered a powerful antiseptic and tonic. Thyme oil serves as a natural preservative with antibacterial activity against a wide spectrum of bacterial classes.','Thyme Oil Red; Unoil TH R; Thyme White; Thymianoel; Thyme Oil; Oleum Thymi; Thymus Vulgaris (Thyme) Oil','Store airtight at room temperature.','[\"25 lb. Pail\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[\"Botanicals\",\"preservatives\\/antimicrobials\",\"essential oils\"]',NULL,'[\"Origin: Natural\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NON REGULATED CHEMICALS NOI CLASS 55\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 145 \\u00f8F\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: NO\",\"Molecular Weight: N\\/A\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10497,'THYME OIL WHITE','103571','GCC','8007-46-3','1','thyme-oil-white','Pale to dark yellow liquid',NULL,'It is widely used in botanical therapy since antiquity for its warming, stimulating, and cleansing properties, it is also considered a powerful antiseptic and tonic. Thyme oil serves as a natural preservative with antibacterial activity against a wide spectrum of bacterial classes.','Thyme Oil White; Thyme Oil Red; Thymianoel; Thyme Oil; Oleum Thymi; Thymus Vulgaris (Thyme) Oil','Store airtight at room temperature.','[\"100 ml. HDPE Bottle\",\"250 ml. HDPE Bottle\",\"5 kg. Pail\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[\"Botanicals\",\"preservatives\\/antimicrobials\",\"essential oils\"]',NULL,'[\"Origin: Natural\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 S 2 CL 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 145 \\u00f8F\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: NO\",\"Molecular Weight: N\\/A\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10498,'THYMOL CRYSTAL NF','103572','GCC','89-83-8','1','thymol-crystal-nf','White crystals with a pungent odor',NULL,'Thymol has antimicrobial activity because of its phenolic structure, and has shown antibacterial activity against bacterial strains including Aeromoans hydrophila and Staphylococcus aureus. In addition Thymol demonstrate confidential post antibacterial effect against some microorganisms. This antibacterial activity is caused by inhibiting growth and lactate production, and by decreasing cellular glucose uptake. Thymol has been used in alcohol solutions and in dusting powders for the treatment of tinea or ringworm infections, and was used in the United States to treat hookworm infections. Thymol can also be used as a medical disinfectant and general purpose disinfectant.','Thymol Crystal NF; Unichem Thymol; 5-Methyl-2 (1-Mehtylethyl)-Phenol-; Thymol Blue Ethanol (50); Thymol Blue TS','Store at room temperature.','[\"100 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"50 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"5 lb. HDPE WM Bottle\",\"2.5 kg. Box\",\"5 kg. HDPE OH Pail\",\"25 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"15 kg. Fiber Drum\",\"20 kg. Box\",\"25 kg. Fiber Drum\",\"30 kg. Fiber Drum\",\"110 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Pharmaceutical\"]','[\"Preservatives\\/antimicrobials\"]','C10H14O','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 216 \\u00f8F\",\"Melting Point: 48-51 \\u00f8C\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 150.22 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10499,'TITANIUM DIOXIDE AND DIMETHICONE','103573','GCC','13463-67-7, 9006-65-9','1','titanium-dioxide-and-dimethicone','White to off-white powder',NULL,'Treating Titanium Dioxide with Dimethicone adds many benefits to cosmetic and skin care products. Using Dimethicone coated powders for both anhydrous and emulsion systems provides numerous benefits for improving cosmetic formulations. The primary benefits are: high water repellency, soft feel and lubricity on skin, better adhesion, higher compressibility and spreadability.','Titanium Dioxide and Dimethicone; T-Cote 031','Store in cool location, keep away from heat and direct sunlight. Keep container sealed.','[\"20 kg. Fiber Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[\"Emulsifiers\",\"surfactants\",\"minerals\"]',NULL,'[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: N\\/A\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 48580 SUB 3 CLASS 55\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: N\\/A\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10500,'TITANIUM DIOXIDE AV-01 SF FOOD GRADE','103574','GCC','13463-67-7','1','titanium-dioxide-av-01-sf-food-grade',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10501,'TITANIUM DIOXIDE COSMETIC WHITE','103575','GCC','13463-67-7','1','titanium-dioxide-cosmetic-white',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10502,'TITANIUM DIOXIDE FOOD GRADE KOSHER POWDER','103576','GCC','13463-67-7','1','titanium-dioxide-food-grade-kosher-powder',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10503,'TITANIUM DIOXIDE MICRONIZED USP POWDER','103577','GCC','13467-67-7','1','titanium-dioxide-micronized-usp-powder',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10504,'TITANIUM DIOXIDE P25','103578','GCC','13463-67-7','1','titanium-dioxide-p25',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10505,'TITANIUM DIOXIDE, TRIMETHOXYCAPRYLYLSILANE','103579','GCC','13463-67-7','1','titanium-dioxide-trimethoxycaprylylsilane',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10506,'TITANIUM DIOXIDE USP BC 3328','103580','GCC','13463-67-7','1'