th witch hazel, thereby helping counter the damaging effects UVA, while acting as an absorber of both UVA and UVB.','Witch Hazel Distillate Preserved with Benzoic Acid; Hamamelis androgyna leaf extract; witch hazel leaf extract','Store in a cool, dry, ventilated location, in a sealed container. Do not store in contact with aluminum, zinc, copper or their alloys.','[\"250 ml. HDPE Bottle\",\"40 lb. Blue TH Pail\",\"55 Gallon Steel Drum\",\"55 Gallon Poly Blue Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[\"Emollient & esters\",\"surfactants\",\"uv absorbers & sunscreens\",\"preservatives\\/antimicrobials\"]',NULL,'[\"Origin: Vegetable\\/Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 3 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: N\\/A\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10604,'WITCH HAZEL EXTRACT 14% AL USP','103683','GCC','64-17-5 Ethonal 14%','1','witch-hazel-extract-14-al-usp','Clear colorless liquid with a characteristic odor',NULL,'It has been approved for use to treat a variety of skin conditions relating to irritation, inflammation and abrasions. It has also been widely accepted for use as a base ingredient in other drug products for chronic skin conditions such as psoriasis, cracked and blistered skin, diaper rash, windburn and sunburn.','Witch Hazel Extract 14% Alcohol USP; T/N Unizel WHA; Hamamelis androgyna leaf extract; witch hazel leaf extract','Store in a cool, dry, ventilated location, in a sealed container. Do not store in contact with aluminum, zinc, copper or their alloys.','[\"250 ml. HDPE Bottle\",\"1 Gallon HDPE NM Jug\",\"41 lb. Blue TH Pail\",\"41 lb. Steel Pail\",\"450 lb. Poly Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Pharmaceutical\"]','[\"Active pharmaceutical ingredient\"]',NULL,'[\"Origin: Vegetable\\/Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 3 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: YES\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: N\\/A\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10605,'XANTHAN GUM','103684','GCC','11138-66-2','1','xanthan-gum','White to cream-white powder','In the oil industry, xanthan gum is used in large quantities, usually to thicken drilling mud. These fluids serve to carry the solids cut by the drilling bit back to the surface.','One of the most remarkable properties of xanthan gum is its ability to produce a large increase in the viscosity of a liquid by adding a very small quantity of gum, on the order of one percent. In foods, xanthan gum is most often found in salad dressings and sauces. It helps to prevent oil separation by stabilizing the emulsion, although it is not an emulsifier. Xanthan gum also helps suspend solid particles, such as spices. Also used in frozen foods and beverages, xanthan gum helps create the pleasant texture in many ice creams, along with guar gum and locust bean gum.','Xanthan Gum; Xantham; Keltrol F; Rhodopol 23; Rhodigel 80 Kosher; Xanthategum','Store in tightly sealed containers in a cool, dry area.','[\"25 kg. Box\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Food & bev.\",\"industrial\"]','[\"Gums\",\"thickener\"]',NULL,'[\"Origin: Vegetable\\/Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 S 2 CL 85\",\"Kosher Status: Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: NO\",\"Molecular Weight: N\\/A\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10606,'XANTHAN GUM FCC DUST FREE K','103685','GCC','11138-66-2','1','xanthan-gum-fcc-dust-free-k','Light cream to tan powder',NULL,'In foods, xanthan gum is most often found in salad dressings and sauces. It helps to prevent oil separation by stabilizing the emulsion, although it is not an emulsifier. Xanthan gum also helps suspend solid particles, such as spices. Also used in frozen foods and beverages, xanthan gum helps create the pleasant texture in many ice creams, along with guar gum and locust bean gum.','Xanthan Gum FCC Dust Free K; Xanthategum; Xanthan Gum; Xantham; Keltrol F; Rhodopol 23','Store in tightly sealed containers in a cool, dry area.','[\"5 lb. HDPE WM Bottle\",\"250 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"5 kg. Pail\",\"25 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"50 lb. Bag\",\"50 lb. Box\",\"50 lb. Fiber Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Food & bev.\"]','[\"Gums\",\"thickener\"]',NULL,'[\"Origin: Vegetable\\/Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: NO\",\"Molecular Weight: N\\/A\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10607,'XANTHAN GUM FOOD GR 80 MESH K','103686','GCC','11138-66-2','1','xanthan-gum-food-gr-80-mesh-k','White or a kind of white crystal powder',NULL,'In foods, xanthan gum is most often found in salad dressings and sauces. It helps to prevent oil separation by stabilizing the emulsion, although it is not an emulsifier. Xanthan gum also helps suspend solid particles, such as spices. Also used in frozen foods and beverages, xanthan gum helps create the pleasant texture in many ice creams, along with guar gum and locust bean gum.','Xanthan Gum Food Grade 80 Mesh K; Xanthan Gum FCC 80 Mesh Kosher; Xanthategum; Xanthan Gum; Xantham; Keltrol F; Rhodopol 23','Store in tightly sealed containers in a cool, dry area.','[\"250 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"5 kg. HDPE OH Pail\",\"25 kg. Bag\",\"25 kg. Fiber Drum\",\"25 kg. Box\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Food & bev.\"]','[\"Gums\",\"thickener\"]',NULL,'[\"Origin: Vegetable\\/Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 S 2 CL 85\",\"Kosher Status: Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: NO\",\"Molecular Weight: N\\/A\"]','2025-04