INSERT INTO `products` VALUES (10637,'ZINC OXIDE USP-3 POWDER','103721','GCC','1314-13-2','1','zinc-oxide-usp-3-powder','White powder','Reflecting the basic properties of ZnO, fine particles of the oxide have deodorizing and antibacterial properties and for that reason are added into materials including cotton fabric, rubber, oral care products, and food packaging. Zinc oxide is widely used to treat a variety of other skin conditions, in products such as baby powder and barrier creams to treat diaper rashes, calamine cream, anti-dandruff shampoos, and antiseptic ointments.','It has been used to protect, soothe, and heal the skin. Zinc oxide provides an excellent barrier to the sun and other irritants. It is somewhat astringent, antiseptic, and antibacterial. When used in sunscreen preparations, it provides both UVA and UVB protection, and can contribute to and/or increase SPF. Zinc oxide is also used when a white color is desired for a product.','Zinc Oxide USP-3 Powder; Zinc Oxide USP-3; T/N: Zinc Oxide USP 3 (Zoco 112); Unichem ZO-50; Zinc white; Calamine; Philosopher’s Wool; Flowers of zinc','Store at room temperature.','[\"250 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"50 lb. Bag\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[\"Minerals\",\"uv absorbers & sunscreens\"]','ZnO','[\"Origin: Natural\\/Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 3 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 S 2 CL 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 1,436 \\u00f8C (2,617 \\u00f8F)\",\"Melting Point: 1,975 \\u00f8C (3,587 \\u00f8F)\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 81.38 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10638,'ZINC PCA','103722','GCC','15454-75-8','1','zinc-pca','White to creamy white powder',NULL,'It is a synthetic skin-conditioning ingredient derived from zinc that has anti-aging benefits due to its ability to suppress collagenase, an enzyme that, left unchecked, breaks down healthy collagen in skin.','Zinc PCA; T/N: Zincidone; Unizin PCA; Zinc Salt; Zinc Salt PCA','Keep containers tightly closed in a cool, dry place.','[\"30 Gram Bottle\",\"50 Gram Bottle\",\"100 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"1 kg. Bottle\",\"5 kg. Box\",\"25 kg. Box\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[\"Moisturizer\",\"humectant\"]','C10H12N2O6Zn','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 5 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 S 2 CL 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: 227.8\\u00f8C\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 129.11 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10639,'ZINC PHENOLSULFONATE OCTAHYDRATE GRANULAR','103723','GCC','127-82-2','1','zinc-phenolsulfonate-octahydrate-granular','Colorless to white crystalline granules',NULL,'It is used in cosmetics and personal care produts as a preservative for antimicrobials, astringent, and deodorant.','Zinc Phenolsulfonate Octahydrate Granular; p-Fenolsolfonate De Zinc; Unichem ZPS; Phenozin; zinc-1,4-phenolsulfonate','Store in a tightly closed container in a dry, well- ventilated place.','[\"250 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"500 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"5 kg. HDPE OH Pail\",\"25 lb. Drum\",\"50 kg. Poly Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Cosmetics\"]','[\"Preservatives\\/antimicrobials\"]','C12H10O8S2Zn8H2O','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: N\\/A\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC48580 S3 CL55\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 411.71 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10640,'ZINC PICOLINATE POWDER','103724','GCC','17949-65-4','1','zinc-picolinate-powder','White fine crystalline powder',NULL,'It is a nutritional/nutraceutical supplement added in food.','Zinc Picolinate Powder; Unipic ZP20; Zinc Picolinate, 200-400 Mesh, Powder; Picolinic acid zinc','Store at room temperature.','[\"50 Gram Bottle\",\"100 Gram HDPE WM Bottle\",\"25 kg. Fiber Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Food & beverage\"]','[\"Nutraceutical supplements\"]','C12H8N2O4Zn','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 S 2 CL 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: N\\/A\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 309.59 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10641,'ZINC PYRION NF','103725','GCC','13463-41-7','1','zinc-pyrion-nf','White powder','Zinc pyrithione is also used as an antibacterial treatment for household sponges, most notably by the 3M Corporation.','Zinc pyrithione is best known for its use in treating dandruff and seborrhoeic dermatitis. It also has antibacterial properties and is effective against many pathogens from the Streptococcus and Staphylococcus genera. Its other medical applications include treatments of psoriasis, eczema, ringworm, fungus, athletes foot, dry skin, atopic dermatitis, tinea, and vitiligo. Due to its low solubility in water zinc pyrithione is suitable for use in outdoor paints and other products that provide protection against mildew and algae. It is an effective algaecide. It is chemically incompatible with paints relying on metal carboxylate curing agents.','Zinc Pyrion NF; Unizene ZP40; bis(2-pyridylthio)zinc 1,1′-dioxide; ZnP; Zinc Omadine','Store in cool, dry conditions in well sealed receptacles.','[\"250 ml. HDPE Bottle\",\"25 kg. Bag\",\"25 kg. Poly Drum\",\"1 lb. Bulk\"]','[\"Cosmetics\",\"pharmaceutical\",\"industrial\"]','[\"Chemicals general\"]','C10H8N2O2S2Zn','[\"Origin: Synthetic\",\"Shelf life: 2 years from mfg. date\",\"Freight Classification: NMFC 43940 SUB 2 CLASS 85\",\"Kosher Status: Not Kosher\",\"Flash Point: N\\/A\",\"Melting Point: 240 \\u00f8C (464 \\u00f8F)\",\"API: NO\",\"Allergen: NO\",\"Hazmat: YES\",\"Molecular Weight: 317.70 g\\/mol\"]','2025-04-10 07:11:58','2025-08-04 14:56:33'),(10642,'ZINC PYRITHIONE 48% AQUEOUS DISPERSION','103726','GCC','13463-41-7','1','zinc-p